Package com.example.mainapplication.datainterface.DataClasses

Class RestaurantHours.RestaurantHour

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.mainapplication.datainterface.DataClasses.RestaurantHours.RestaurantHour
  • Enclosing class:
    RestaurantHours
    private class RestaurantHours.RestaurantHour
extends java.lang.Object
    The RestaurantHour class is a data class that holds the hours of a restaurant for a specific day It is a sub class of RestaurantHours and is used to store 1 section of hours for a restaurant as well as the section name
    Author:
    Ryan Leska
